Ethics aside, your cat may not go after the prey if you feed it well or may just play with it. I had some cats that were originally wild and also tried to keep some mice around in a glass enclosure. The cats had to be kept far away from the mice because they would go berserk trying to get in after them. Due to bad bedding, the mice died three days later and we never got any more mice. Our cats continued to be avid mousers long into their old age. Don't over feed your animals if you want them to keep their prey drive up. Did you know a lot of dogs are very happy to receive mice as treats and will go mousing if they can catch them? Some friends had a pet husky who had to be watched around their pet rats because she would gobble them up by the gulp. The husky would get super affectionate if she though you would give her a mouse to eat.
